p: Vita CAD-Temp is composed, according to the manufacturer, of PMMA or poly (methyl 2-methylpropenoate) (C 5O 2H 8), silicon dioxide, pigments and MPRP (microfilled reinforced polyacrylate). In EDS analysis, we detected carbon and oxygen, as well as sulfur and silicon. As we know, carbon is the main element of PMMA chains, but we can also find other elements such as hydrogen, oxygen, nitrogen, chlorine, sulfur or fluorine. In this case, hydrogen was not detected [ 45]. The Vita CAD-Temp manufacturer assert there is no residual monomer in CAD/CAM polymerization and we couldnâ€™t find it either.
